snippet.textDisplay:
Back in 2012 I had a lot of trouble with sleep deprivation (I will not speak about the specific reasons tho) and the longest I have stayed awake was almost 9 days before I just passed out from exhaustion.
And I can absolutely confirm those side effects.
I distinctly remember walking through my hometown and being profoundly convinced everyone who bullied me in school was stalking me and calling me names. I could hear them no matter what I did, no matter where I went to and I would always see vague schemes of what I assumed to be them in my peripheral field of vision. But as soon as I turned around they were gone.
Before that I was extremely aggressive towards some of my closest friends and apparently threatened to harm them (I myself can't remember that at all).
I was paranoid and scared shitless. It took months for me to recover from that time.

snippet.textDisplay: I clicked on this video because I have something similar, and had a situation in which, were it not for the EMS, I wouldn't type this, back in October 2019. I have never faced communism, nor being a refugee, however after abruptly stopping taking xanax, I had a reaction that I wouldn't possible wish it on anyway. The last thing I remember was my body arching backwards, my airways closing up and that was that. And all throughout that just...Fear. No face to it, no shape, form. A fear that humbled me to never say a mean word to anyone, to never upset or sadden anyone. The medical report is not conclusive, although there was an indication as to the xanax intake and abrupt stopping to it. Ever since October, everytime I need to sleep I have to take one gerodorm and one trittico. Were I not to take those two, I either cannot sleep, I microsleep (less than 15 minutes), or I fall asleep for an hour and having sleep paralysis, waking up continuously in a dream. But not in real life. I wanted to ask for help from my physician, but with the pandemic going on, I think I can wait. There are no monsters, no demons, no angels, neither when I required resuscitation from the EMS, reopening my airways, neither in these sleep paralysis situations, and while I'm very prone to comedy and fun and as much happiness as I can get and offer, I'm carrying this since last year. But although my sleep is really crap, thank you for giving me this for the awake hours. And thank you for making this, I didn't know where to share my experience, this place might be as good as any. Love your and Steph's work and charitable efforts. Hugs from Romania.
